<meta
    desc="Mana Type: Poison"
    status="DRAFT"
><>

<title>Poison Mana<>

<content>
    <section> Introduction <>
        <p>Poison mana is a type of mana which is harvested from all the toxic and deadly compounds
        found in plants, trees, in the ground, etc... Poison casters are good at causing debilitating status
        effects to their opponents, and making them unable to fight back.<>
        <p>Poison mana has an affinity with <a t="#mana_*_death">#<> and <a t="#mana_*_vine">#<>.<>

    <section> Caster Types <>
        <heading level="1">Poison Manipulator<>
        <p>Vine <a t="#mana_*_manipulators">manipulators<> can create deadly clouds of poison vapours and create
        different poisons which cause damage, decay and death to their enemies.<>
        <p>In the presence of different poisonous substances, poison manipulators can use those poisons as a source as
        well, but it will be that poison's effect.<>

        <heading level="1">Poison Armorers<>
        <p>Poison <a t="#mana_*_armorers">armorers<> cover themselves in a noxious miasma which make enemies think
        twice about attacking you. This is also used to damage opponents with physical strikes.<>
        <p>In the presence of poisons, they can make their armour out of that poison too.<>

        <heading level="1">Poison Animators<>
        <p>Poison <a t="#mana_*_animators">animators<> create poison elementals to do their bidding. Poison elementals
        are like clouds of gas or liquid that go around trying to surround and infect their masters' enemies.<>
        <p>In the presence of poisons, they can make elementals from those poisons too.<>

        <heading level="1">Poison Item Wielders<>
        <p>Poison <a t="#mana_*_itemWielders">item wielders<> wield items that emit poisons and toxins. Examples
        include poisoned weapons and toxin grenades.<>
<>
